<aura:component extends="auradocs:topicPanel">
    <aura:set attribute="title" value="Converter Interface"/>

<p>The Converter interface is a type converter that converts a value from one Java type to another Java type. You can implement this interface to provide a custom converter for your own custom type for converting data sent from the client to the server, such as input parameters of server-side controller actions or component attributes.</p>

<auradocs:info>Standard types are automatically converted and don't require custom converters.</auradocs:info>

<table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
<thead>
    <tr>
        <th>Name</th>  
        <th>Parameters</th>      
        <th>Return Type</th>
        <th>Description</th>
    </tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
    <td><code>convert</code></td>
    <td>Original Type <i>value</i></td>
    <td>Converted Type</td>
    <td>Converts the specified value from its original Java type to the target Java type and returns the converted value.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><code>getFrom</code></td>
    <td></td>
    <td>Original Type</td>
    <td>Returns the original Java type of the value.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><code>getTo</code></td>
    <td></td>
    <td>Converted Type</td>
    <td>Returns the Java type that the value is to be converted to.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><code>getToParameters</code></td>
    <td>Original Type <i>value</i></td>
    <td>Converted Type</td>
    <td>Returns the Java type parameters of a target type that is a parameterized type. If the target type is not parameterized, returns <code>null</code>.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p><b>See also:</b><br/>    
    <auradocs:topicLink topic="registerCustomConverter">Registering a Custom Converter</auradocs:topicLink>
</p>
</aura:component>
